    "name": "Stonefish",
    "type": "creature",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Stonefish",
            "type": "section",
            "text": "Stonefish use their superior camouflage to lie in wait and devour small prey, becoming indistinguishable from the reefs they call home. Larger creatures are also at risk, although mostly through accidental contact with the stonefish's spines and their agonizing venom.",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Howl of the Wild",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Howl of the Wild pg. 148",
                        "alt": "Howl of the Wild pg. 148",
                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                        "aonid": 226
                    },
                    "page": 148,
                    "errata": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "2.1",
                        "alt": "2.1",
                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                        "aonid": 226
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Fish",
            "type": "section",
            "text": "These magnificent creatures hide beneath the surface of the calm lakes, flowing rivers, and vast seas. The water is their domain, and some are quite protective of their home.",
